<subSubSection id="8772B7EFD2609A110226FC012B912B86" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="A121DEB68E12CD4CCFF6BA5B38A213FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="86448A0B775AD97991E957E24C8044EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
The reason to reduce the status of 
<taxonomicName id="0BC3E41E8EDCADC8A4DC7CDE23D4BF43" authorityName=", stat. resurr." baseAuthorityName="Yasumatsu" baseAuthorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Hoplisoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="distinguendus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distinguendus">
<emphasis id="B535333AE062DCD68E6ABA2EB99BE897" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">distinguendus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to rank of subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="CADCA731D54C73A2A6B1B40CCBE70AFE" baseAuthorityName="Handlirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Hoplisoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="gazagnairei" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gazagnairei">
<emphasis id="DEDB7EDD1A4B248DDCB44246E3BE866E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">gazagnairei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was, most likely, a similar form of males clypeus (apical part of the clypeus concave). The modified clypeus is not unique for these two taxa: clypeus with separated apical part present in the North American 
<taxonomicName id="533AE18AB97C3231141B7FBC3358EDAB" baseAuthorityName="Handlirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Hoplisoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hoplisoides hamatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">
<emphasis id="50E1DD6C7C88B93AE32F1F40919B8856" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Hoplisoides hamatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Handlirsch, 1888), 
<taxonomicName id="58AD3B820F3181E593E7C7EF3EBD6734" genus="H." lsidName="H. nebulosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rank="species" species="nebulosus">
<emphasis id="93E417AD0070F45D71AED62AEB66F827" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">H. nebulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Packard, 1867), 
<taxonomicName id="4A06BFD4A58DCAA10CB7AE19C2DA09EB" genus="H." lsidName="H. placidus" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rank="species" species="placidus">
<emphasis id="50AE4F83F044FCDFBD884D0CDDAE28D8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">H. placidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(F. Smith, 1856) and 
<taxonomicName id="E6E4F9AEEFE8A2226DEE75A84B18A176" genus="H." lsidName="H. punctifrons" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rank="species" species="punctifrons">
<emphasis id="0BB77528063506DD801C1FEAC070BBC5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">H. punctifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Cameron, 1890) (Buck, 2007). Besides, 
<taxonomicName id="4000E3E0192735400C97DFDD4B5559B3" genus="H." lsidName="H. gazagnairei" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rank="species" species="gazagnairei">
<emphasis id="524431C22479B6E465FFCED96A271D8E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">H. gazagnairei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9073E95D071C91408755726EBEDF0B26" genus="H." lsidName="H. distinguendus" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rank="species" species="distinguendus">
<emphasis id="1C71A1A1EF601AFF47AB9A661186BE44" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">H. distinguendus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have many significant differences (besides coloration), given in the Table 
<tableCitation id="FC3F57817C6F94CBFF2738F494344AA0" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Comparison of morphological features of Hoplisoides gazagnairei and H. distinguendus." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/2C974E84F8176D368E717DB94BB43958" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" tableUuid="2C974E84F8176D368E717DB94BB43958">1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="2C974E84F8176D368E717DB94BB43958" ID-Table-UUID="2C974E84F8176D368E717DB94BB43958" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/2C974E84F8176D368E717DB94BB43958" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" start="Table 1" startId="T1">
