<td id="96F1B3F8319CBF2DE721B9B01F6A1032" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">Propodeum</td>
<td id="0AE0074F8B44022027D3FFA7F4340B71" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
dorsolaterally with coarse punctation and rugose sculpture; gibbous; edges of metapostnotum poorly visible (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6ECEF25B3B04C2C22EA3B43934CF62D1" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-C), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (D-F), males: A, D clypeus, frontolateral view B, E scutellum, metanotum and propodeum, posterolateral view C, F metasoma, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469676" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">5B</figureCitation>
)
</td>
<td id="B1D73C11E97871E80218078CFF4276DE" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
dorsolaterally smooth, with space not large punctation; uniformly convex; metapostnotum clearly separated (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="88880BCBA966DAC8B1411AD56C6BEEAD" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-C), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (D-F), males: A, D clypeus, frontolateral view B, E scutellum, metanotum and propodeum, posterolateral view C, F metasoma, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469676" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">5E</figureCitation>
)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="BA4B9FB6E17D8167DDC3B17BD774BE67" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<td id="3B5AF78B5D77F393A2130A505611DE60" colspan="3" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
<emphasis id="6F3E9FCAAAC2C788A6744F546D47CCF8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Males</emphasis>
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="A73650038E0B938822BBB4990BBF49AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<td id="4EF31CF0F03F81F49DE3112737D15415" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">Apicoposterior spine on male hind tarsomeres 1-3</td>
<td id="418E95561AE345C677FF7712ACC95DBA" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">as long as apicoanterior spine</td>
<td id="6FB23EF97CD71B73AE14120FD820C9F5" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
2-3 times longer than apicoanterior spine (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="57478F2779DC3287D2D65E3E44A04B53" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-B), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (C-F), males: A, C antenna, dorsal view B, D foretarsus, dorsal view E midtarsus, dorsal view F hindtarsus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469677" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">6F</figureCitation>
)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="CC31A891F8855498EA789AF986AA6A23" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<td id="38E0DE7E7B5FDE4FB2E237D82A28842A" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">Clypeus</td>
<td id="CCC13B95936627AFE50EDC47F7C9E1A6" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
apical margin with median weak bilobate protrusion; lateral setae not combined into brush (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="05D910C9633948D72769944B24A4101F" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-C), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (D-F), males: A, D clypeus, frontolateral view B, E scutellum, metanotum and propodeum, posterolateral view C, F metasoma, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469676" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">5A</figureCitation>
)
</td>
<td id="A21DDF10BB8AC0E8BC689F61A4558FA8" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
apical margin without median protrusion, with simple wide excision; lateral setae combined into thin brush (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4C3CC51012BAE4C373B85891E336038F" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-C), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (D-F), males: A, D clypeus, frontolateral view B, E scutellum, metanotum and propodeum, posterolateral view C, F metasoma, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469676" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">5D</figureCitation>
)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="46FDF7D73AAA23D107B2B11DA34B83A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<td id="F169B443412B2113DC01C16E93F45F9D" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">Antenna</td>
<td id="3D5584CA589F570C05A30618818FA21C" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
flagellomeres shorter, F10-F11 visibly transverse, F12 ratio length to width near 1.4 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="190FADA9FF9B7D659FAAF920A78FE58C" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-B), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (C-F), males: A, C antenna, dorsal view B, D foretarsus, dorsal view E midtarsus, dorsal view F hindtarsus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469677" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">6A</figureCitation>
)
</td>
<td id="5C450FBDDFBF2F4CB36CD9E9C4BA98C6" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
flagellomeres longer, F10 cubelike, F11 longer whan wide, F12 ratio length to width near 1.9 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FF5AD88004FC61EF660FA05C0E8DA615" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-B), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (C-F), males: A, C antenna, dorsal view B, D foretarsus, dorsal view E midtarsus, dorsal view F hindtarsus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469677" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">6C</figureCitation>
)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="43C9E3FF20031296B0904A3E05FF8B4B" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<td id="FB54CBB27F983440A2BAEBC47D1B55C0" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">Foretarsomeres 2-4</td>
<td id="4B0D3B8C4E014CC314B62EDBD22AA188" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
transverse (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1E7F4CBA68D361CBB60F36B48270AF44" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-B), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (C-F), males: A, C antenna, dorsal view B, D foretarsus, dorsal view E midtarsus, dorsal view F hindtarsus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469677" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">6B</figureCitation>
)
</td>
<td id="FE8553DBDAC2CE4D9C712F7EBBA9E046" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
strongly transverse (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="269BC6A6984D5931CF6A2C7780C66CEF" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-B), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (C-F), males: A, C antenna, dorsal view B, D foretarsus, dorsal view E midtarsus, dorsal view F hindtarsus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469677" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">6D</figureCitation>
)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="82AB9B55A1626E59D1F858A34BAEF589" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<td id="B6A7CA3E134CAB49D5B4E8E2D2E5A207" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">Midtarsomeres 2 and 3</td>
<td id="707A6871078D090716D3B031BF6BE154" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">symmetrical, not modified</td>
<td id="0C132852557DCCFEDB67B14FAC417D3B" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">
strongly asymmetrical, tarsomer 2 with long process apicoposteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="009DEB716DC71307B37D8B0BBE51A3F9" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Hoplisoides gazagnairei (Handlirsch) from Tunisia [FSCV] (A-B), and H. distinguendus (Yasumatsu) from Buryatia, Russia [FSCV] (C-F), males: A, C antenna, dorsal view B, D foretarsus, dorsal view E midtarsus, dorsal view F hindtarsus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.56839.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469677" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">6E</figureCitation>
)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="A526772A901332D9E31026FF80B0BD0F" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<td id="9A494BC48C917B7451F7A47D76785AE8" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">Metasomal tergum 1</td>
<td id="8D9714191C26BF66F93513E000B25F53" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">as long as wide (dorsal view)</td>
<td id="1AD8220A9B5EF4EC8855389CCC0B7508" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">distinctly longer than wide (dorsal view)</td>
</tr>
<tr id="465FF2359D7FBD4CE8C032B5F74C5497" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<td id="6B0CBFC25E57FEF55838A27988D0E78D" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">Metasomal tergum 2</td>
<td id="7DB5C734929EDE340ED493A3967740A8" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">thickened at base, slightly concave behind the thickening (lateral view)</td>
<td id="370EF59677FD489EC8413F45B8C28C5A" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">not thickened, uniformly slightly convex</td>
</tr>
<tr id="0C4C676C4F2AF76C13167E21FF269110" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<td id="DE1F494C9B98456BFC789750A0BD12DE" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">Metasomal sternum 6</td>
<td id="ECB861F69DAA75518970F15111DB729A" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">strongly convex</td>
<td id="EEFACC5E7D7A0D7E72A10DF4FC402C7C" colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rowspan="1">almost flat</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="220E2DF8858EBE84C24223B3D4D66ED7" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
Based on the above differences and the huge geographical hiatus, we consider 
<taxonomicName id="C2B57A0CF29CFFD54E08A348FCD2BAAD" baseAuthorityName="Handlirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Hoplisoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hoplisoides gazagnairei" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gazagnairei">
<emphasis id="C5EF04339E1AE20B478C995E6F47DD74" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Hoplisoides gazagnairei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Handlirsch, 1893) and 
<taxonomicName id="2691F5C0BE6BAA184716E2EF85B1A3BD" genus="H." lsidName="H. distinguendus" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" rank="species" species="distinguendus">
<emphasis id="C3BDA03F808A232DE2A2735B75B421DA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">H. distinguendus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Yasumatsu, 1939) as different species.
</paragraph>
